    "summary": "Samsara Telematics exposes per-vehicle snapshot, history, and feed access for GPS, engine state, odometer, fault-code, fuel, and auxiliary-input readings, making it the primary read surface for fleet location and onboard diagnostic telemetry.",
    "description": "Manufactured OpenAPI artifact for Telematics. This file was synthesized by Last Mile from curated research JSON and is not vendor-certified. Use it as an agent-consumable starting point, then validate paths, schemas, authentication, and server URLs with the vendor before production use. The Telematics guide documents three read surfaces over the same vehicle stats model: `GET /fleet/vehicles/stats` for current snapshots, `GET /fleet/vehicles/stats/history` for backfill or time-range queries, and `GET /fleet/vehicles/stats/feed` for cursor-based synchronization. The documented stat types include GPS, engine states, OBD and GPS odometer values, fault codes, fuel levels, engine runtime, and many other diagnostics, which makes this the deepest Samsara product for operational telemetry extraction.",
